# Data Handling Policy

## Repository Profile

This repository is public-facing governance material and must remain conservative.


## Do not commit

- secrets
- credentials
- tokens
- certificates
- private keys
- customer data
- employee data
- raw private source packets used during curation

## Allowed content types

- governance text
- prompts
- templates
- examples that are sanitized
- conservative usage statements already supported by repository policy

## Publication rule

When in doubt, omit sensitive or source-specific detail rather than paraphrasing it into a potentially disclosive artifact
